American cultural influence in Japan is important because it's an example of an issue which decides if American citizens themselves feel like New Testament era Romans or if the US just provides the rest of the world with a huge market under a trade deficit.

It's the same reason the US army still justifies its budget by pointing to them winning the world war and they have to keep producing propaganda movies like Oppenheimer almost a century later. And why facts like certain Japanese families lobbying to keep US bases there feel wrong

The good thing is that actual American culture like Joseph McElroy novels do not rely on fraud and if anything the death of the superficial and astroturfed aspects of US media dying will make space for this secret core emerging to the open.
